#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The National Institute for Communicable Diseases (NICD) has reported 6,527 new COVID-19 cases. The NICD has also reported one more COVID-19 related death. READ: SAPS mask supplier slapped with R3.4m fine Gauteng leads with 2,789 cases, followed by KwaZulu-Natal with 1,724 infections. Meanwhile, South Africa is not yet in a fifth wave. However the country has seen a steady increase in COVID-19 infections. The Health Department's Nicholas Crisp says they are working with various teams to make sure new regulations governing the management of COVID-19 will be in place by 5 May. Watch the video above for more details on this story. #COVID19 UPDATE: 30,334 tests were conducted in the last 24hrs, with 6,527 new cases, representing a 21.5% positivity rate. Today @HealthZA reports 3 deaths; of these 1 occurred in the past 24 – 48 hours. Total fatalities are 100,363 to date.See more here: https://t.co/GMHID6tSL1 pic.twitter.com/sw4tYuBNu5